</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1324C7C0FFF2E35EE7B4F9C7FD21F9B2" box="[650,714,1614,1638]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1947,1969]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,185,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,182,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Exilisia spp.: male (7–9) and female (10) genitalia. 7, E. ngai, holotype, Kenya, slide NHMUK010315783 Volynkin (©NHMUK); 8, E. smithi, holotype, Liberia, slide AV5111 Volynkin; 9, E. bipuncta, lectotype, S Africa, slide BMNH(E) Arct. 494 (©NHMUK); 10, E. smithi, paratype, Liberia, slide AV5145 Volynkin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3785784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3785784/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) differs clearly from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE133F9C6FB63F9B2" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1037,1160,1614,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipuncta">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE133F9C6FB63F9B2" box="[1037,1160,1614,1638]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. bipuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1324C7C0FFF2E35EE1A6F9C7FB31F9B2" box="[1176,1242,1614,1638]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1947,1969]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,185,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,182,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Exilisia spp.: male (7–9) and female (10) genitalia. 7, E. ngai, holotype, Kenya, slide NHMUK010315783 Volynkin (©NHMUK); 8, E. smithi, holotype, Liberia, slide AV5111 Volynkin; 9, E. bipuncta, lectotype, S Africa, slide BMNH(E) Arct. 494 (©NHMUK); 10, E. smithi, paratype, Liberia, slide AV5145 Volynkin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3785784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3785784/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EA6B4FFF2E35EE1D8F9C7FA86F9B2" author="Kuhne, L." box="[1254,1389,1614,1638]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" pagination="353 - 394" refId="ref3137" refString="Kuhne, L. (2007) Beschreibung neuer Flechtenbarenarten aus Afrika nebst taxonomischen Anmerkungen (Arctiidae: Lithosiinae). Esperiana Memoir, 3, 353 - 394. [in German]" type="journal article" year="2007">Kühne 2007</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 52) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE5D1F9FAFE65F95E" authorityName="Kuhne" authorityYear="2007" box="[239,398,1651,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominentia">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE5D1F9FAFE65F95E" box="[239,398,1651,1674]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. prominentia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EA6B4FFF2E35EE70FF9FBFD53F95E" author="Kuhne, L." box="[561,696,1650,1674]" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" pagination="353 - 394" refId="ref3137" refString="Kuhne, L. (2007) Beschreibung neuer Flechtenbarenarten aus Afrika nebst taxonomischen Anmerkungen (Arctiidae: Lithosiinae). Esperiana Memoir, 3, 353 - 394. [in German]" type="journal article" year="2007">Kühne 2007</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 53) by its longer and narrower left subapical costal process (that is broader and shorter in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE49EF91EFDF1F97A" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[416,538,1686,1710]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipuncta">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE49EF91EFDF1F97A" box="[416,538,1686,1710]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. bipuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE770F91EFD07F97A" authorityName="Kuhne" authorityYear="2007" box="[590,748,1687,1710]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominentia">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE770F91EFD07F97A" box="[590,748,1687,1710]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. prominentia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), smaller right subapical costal process, more robust right apical costal process with a broad arrow-shaped tip (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE7AAF932FCE5F906" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[660,782,1722,1746]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipuncta">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE7AAF932FCE5F906" box="[660,782,1722,1746]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. bipuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE67EF932FC36F906" authorityName="Kuhne" authorityYear="2007" box="[832,989,1723,1746]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominentia">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE67EF932FC36F906" box="[832,989,1723,1746]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. prominentia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that is narrow, finger like), and longer and curved right distal saccular process with a club-like broadened tip (that is short, directed distally and has a tapered tip in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE5A9F88AFEF9F8CE" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[151,274,1794,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipuncta">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE5A9F88AFEF9F8CE" box="[151,274,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. bipuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a foot-shaped tip in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE725F88AFD52F8CE" authorityName="Kuhne" authorityYear="2007" box="[539,697,1795,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominentia">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE725F88AFD52F8CE" box="[539,697,1795,1818]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. prominentia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In addition, the band-like fused transtillae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE18EF88AFB16F8CE" authorityName="Volynkin" authorityYear="2020" box="[1200,1277,1795,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ngai">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE18EF88AFB16F8CE" box="[1200,1277,1795,1818]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. ngai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are longer and more heavily sclerotised, the left apical costal process is narrower, the left distal saccular process is well developed (that is absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE424F8C2FE7DF8B6" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[282,406,1866,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipuncta">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE424F8C2FE7DF8B6" box="[282,406,1866,1890]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. bipuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the right subapical saccular process is shorter and much broader compared to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE0BBF8C2FF1FF852" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipuncta">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE0BBF8C2FF1FF852" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. bipuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Compared to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE4AEF8E6FDC6F852" authorityName="Kuhne" authorityYear="2007" box="[400,557,1903,1926]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominentia">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE4AEF8E6FDC6F852" box="[400,557,1903,1926]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. prominentia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE629F8E6FC88F852" authorityName="Volynkin" authorityYear="2020" box="[791,867,1903,1926]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ngai">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE629F8E6FC88F852" box="[791,867,1903,1926]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. ngai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also characterized by its narrower tip of saccus, left distal saccular process being narrower basally and twisted and blunt apically (that is broad basally and thorn-like apically in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE58DF83EFEBAF81A" authorityName="Kuhne" authorityYear="2007" box="[179,337,1975,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominentia">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE58DF83EFEBAF81A" box="[179,337,1975,1998]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. prominentia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the presence of right distal and subapical saccular processes (both are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FA0C6FFF2E35EE1D8F83EFA6EF81A" authorityName="Kuhne" authorityYear="2007" box="[1254,1413,1975,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Exilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="596" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominentia">
<emphasis id="B96B0757FFF2E35EE1D8F83EFA6EF81A" box="[1254,1413,1975,1998]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="596">E. prominentia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
